{"comments":"Unit quaternions for 3D rotation representation.\n\n## Proof References\nAll operations correspond to proven theorems in `proofs/Hydrogen/Math/Quaternion.lean`:\n- mul_assoc: Quaternion multiplication is associative\n- mul_identity_left/right: identity × q = q × identity = q\n- conjugate_mul: (ab)* = b*a*\n- lengthSq_mul: ‖ab‖² = ‖a‖² × ‖b‖²\n- mul_isUnit: Unit quaternions closed under multiplication\n- normalize_isUnit: Normalized quaternions are unit\n\n## Why Quaternions\n- No gimbal lock (unlike Euler angles)\n- Smooth interpolation via SLERP\n- Compact representation (4 floats vs 9 for rotation matrix)\n- Numerically stable composition\n\n## Mathematical Background\nQuaternions extend complex numbers: q = w + xi + yj + zk\nwhere i² = j² = k² = ijk = -1\n\nUnit quaternions (‖q‖ = 1) form a double cover of SO(3):\nboth q and -q represent the same rotation.\n\nRotation of vector v by quaternion q: v' = qvq⁻¹\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[112,29],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Rotation/Quaternion.purs","start":[112,17]},"title":"Quaternion"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Rotation","Quaternion"],"Quaternion"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[115,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Dimension/Rotation/Quaternion.purs","start":[115,1]},"title":"eqQuaternion"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","depen